data.title: John & Evangeline
data.meta_description: Re-live the beauty that was John and Evangeline from One LIfe to Live as portrayed by Michael Easton and Renee Goldsberry!
data.text:
From the moment these two first met in Angel Square to discuss a case for which they were on opposite sides, there were sparks. But would One Life to Live go there? Most didn’t think so due in part to the obvious, Evangeline being African-American and John being white one of the most popular male leads on the show, who already had a “soul mate”🙄😒 in Natalie Buchanan. African-American women were just not paired with the male lead of a show. Well they did go there. First with a dare kiss, then a game of pool, a bottle of wine and a locked basement door that led to one of hottest love scenes in daytime history. Vangie and John decided that their night together in that locked basement was just too much wine and thus a “one-time thing”, but then they slept together again and it turned into a “two-time thing.” They quickly became friends with benefits (FWB), which soon led to lunch dates, movie dates and eventually “some strings” i.e. double dates, football games, an exchange of house keys and a him giving her his mother’s pearls. The natural progression of their interactions from FWB to a real relationship was interesting and grown-up and their chemistry was FIRE🔥 . These two had the potential to become one of the most popular couples on the show, but the writers torpedoed that potential with their need to return to the old and tired status quo. John was reunited with Natalie Buchanan, who he wasn’t even lukewarm about, and Evangeline was shuffled off to Cristian Vega, an unemployed artist who was beneath her, with her and John never to be revisited again. Its truly a shame because it can’t be said enough how much these two sizzled and their lives could and did make sense together. I still smile at what these two were and sigh 😔 at what could’ve been.

“I have been praying my entire life for the opportunity to stand in front of the world and say “Thank you” to my parents who are here tonight, Ron and Betty. Hamilton has been one “once in a lifetime” moment after another, and still the best moment of every day is going home every night to my husband, Alexis, I love you very much. I would like to thank Tommy and Lin and Jeffrey and Jill and Sandy and Oscar and Lorie and Nina and Lily and Brian, thank you. I would like to thank the entire company of Hamilton, when one of us wins, we all win because we are one. I love you. And lastly, I would just love to say, that if you know anything about me, I’ve spent the last 10 years of my life with what some would consider the life blood of a woman’s career, just trying to have children. I get to testify in front of all of you, that the Lord gave me Benjamin and Brielle, and then He still gave me this!!”
